<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TOYS-FORECAST-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LIST PREVIEWS COOL YULE GIFTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY DAVE MCNARY  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- There are 93 shopping days until Christmas.
</P>
<P>
   If that fact sends chills up your spine, you must be a parent
who has tried _ and probably failed _ to get the toy in each of the
past few holiday seasons.
</P>
<P>
   Jim Silver, not only a veteran toy tracker but also a father of
three, has set out to ease the pain for parents and children
through publication of the Toy Wishes catalog with reviews of more
than 1,000 toys. More importantly, Silver has singled out the Hot
Dozen that will disappear fastest from store shelves.
</P>
<P>
   Anyone who has hung around children will recognize most names on
the list: Barbie, Buzz Lightyear, Elmo, Furbys, ``Star Wars,'' WCW,
WWF and Pokemon. Silver predicts two others, Amazing Amy and the
Intel Play QX3 Computer Microscope, could reach blockbuster status.
</P>
<P>
   Except for the pair of Pokemon entries, a plush toy and a new
set of cards, everything on the list uses computer electronics.
``Kids are growing up a lot faster these days, and they expect
more,'' Silver said.
</P>
<P>
   American parents will spend nearly $20 billion on toys during
the next three months, Silver estimates. He said his goal is a
simple one: ``to help them better spend their money so their kids
say `cool' when they open their gifts.''
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
