<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Somewhere in the world is the
secret headquarters of a powerful coalition of citizens who come
from all walks of life and yet share the single-minded goal to
prevent popular technological advances. (Nethaway, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ I find it highly amusing that
Sheryl McCarthy, a columnist for Newsday, is all worked up about
the ``male sexual fantasy'' surrounding the Miss America Pageant.
Hey, lady, get a grip. The male sexual fantasy ain't watching some
18-year-old from Mississippi play ``Ode to Joy'' out of tune on a
French horn. If you ladies want to get your skirts in a knot about
who gets to enter the Miss America Pageant and who doesn't, don't
drag us guys into the argument. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CERABINO-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Max Gordon is 90.
Mollie Levy is 82. And between them they have six children, 14
grandchildren and 17 great-grandchildren. But in Florida, their new
union is just another potential bad marriage, a marriage that needs
safeguarding by the Marriage Preparation and Preservation Act of
1998. (Cerabino, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The dispatcher stayed on
the line for 11 minutes. Eleven long minutes. Through the thumping
up the stairs. Through his yells. Through her screams, shrill,
eerie shrieks that erupted from the depths of a frightened woman's
soul. She stayed on through the gunshots. ``Hello,'' she kept
saying. ``Hello. Hello. Hello.'' A domestic violence call. (Minor,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
