<P>
   BUYER'S-EDGE _ In metro Atlanta, it's hard to miss the car alarm
chorus. From flashing lights to honking horns to synthesized voices
stating, ``ARMED _ DISARMED,'' they've caught our attention. And
for good reason. According to the Highway Loss Data Institute
(HLDI), anti-theft devices reduce the risk of your vehicle being
stolen. Which means those noisemakers really do work. We take a
look at various kinds of anti-theft devices: how they work, what's
available and what they cost. 14 inch main story and lots of
breakouts. (Brooks, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40. WITH PHOTOS.
