<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on Keanu Reeves (``The Matrix'')
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Bill &AMP; Ted's Excellent Adventure.'' Tripping through time to
prepare for a history test.
</P>
<P>
   ``My Own Private Idaho.'' Mouthing Shakespeare in Gus Van Sant's
fascinating, flawed look at the relationship between two hustlers
(Reeves and River Phoenix).
</P>
<P>
   ``Bram Stoker's Dracula.'' Trying out a British accent, sort of,
in Francis Ford Coppola's phantasmagoria.
</P>
<P>
   ``Speed.'' Riding one fast bus with Sandra Bullock in this
nail-biter.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Devil's Advocate.'' Finding out the hard way that his boss
(Al Pacino) really is the Evil One.
</P>
<P>
   Notable videos now on sale
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  DVD: ``Heavy,'' $27.95; ``Someone to Watch Over Me,'' $24.95.
``Breakfast at Tiffany's,'' ``Barefoot in the Park,'' $29.99.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Family: ``Something Wicked This Way Comes,'' $14.98 VHS,
$24.98 DVD.
</P>
<P>
   ``Labyrinth,'' $14.95 VHS.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Audrey Hepburn: ``My Fair Lady,'' ``How to Steal a Million,''
``Two for the Road,'' $14.98 each.
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
