   BARBECUE HEAVEN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LOCKHART, Texas _ The old Kreutz Market was dark and ancient. It
was a smoky shrine to Texas barbecue, and worshippers came from all
corners of the state to fill themselves with the glorious products
of its pits. Now, the ``new'' Kreutz Market _ just blocks from the
old _ is a bright, shining cathedral. The change was due to a
family scrape that has been duly chronicled. It was a
brother-sister thing, and no one can expect a brother and sister to
get along forever. By ART CHAPMAN. Story will move in ``d'' food
and dining category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
