<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Bill Bradley's apparent strategy of trying to energize
liberals during the primary campaign without coming off as a
radical left-winger seemed to be working perfectly until he
unveiled two proposals: amending the 1964 Civil Rights Act to ban
discrimination against homosexuals, and changing military
regulations to allow gays to serve openly in the armed forces. By
BILL THOMPSON. Story will move in ``k'' commentary category &QL; 
 &QL; 
