<SLUG> BC-KIDS:BOOKS:GOOD-SPORTS-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>

 BOOK REVIEW: ``GOOD SPORTS: WINNING, LOSING, AND EVERYTHING IN
BETWEEN''
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
 World rights.
 By KELLY KENNEDY, (Home School) Student Reporter
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOOK: ``Good Sports: Winning, Losing, and Everything in
Between''
</P>
<P>
   Author: Therese Kauchak.
</P>
<P>
   Illustrator: Norm Bendell.
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: Pleasant Company Publications.
</P>
<P>
   Ages: 8 and older.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $8.95.
</P>
<P>
   Summary: ``Good Sports'' is every girl's personal sports
playbook. It gives you everything from a brief history of girls in
sports to interviews with such famous athletes as U.S. women's
soccer player Julie Foudy; Nikki McCray, from the WNBA; Michelle
Kwan, Olympic figure skater; and 13-year-old swimmer Kalyn Keller.
</P>
<P>
   This book also has fun quizzes, pages to write your sports
memories, lists of sites on the Internet to get more information on
your favorite sports and insights on what boys and girls think
about playing on co-ed teams.
</P>
<P>
   Comments: After reading ``Good Sports,'' I was ready to go out
on a mile jog. Well, not really, but it does get you pumped up and
ready for fall sports. It has entertaining drawings that, when
combined with all the other great features, make for a pretty fun
read.
</P>
<P>
   I found one word that may be offensive to some folks and an
unnecessary illustration of a mean Gremlin-type creature. I was
kind of surprised and disappointed to see things like that in an
American Girls Library book.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 8.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; -0-
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)
</P>
</TEXT>
