COLANGELO (Phoenix) - Jerry Colangelo is not looking for a
big-money partner, but he is looking for ways to get more value
from his franchises and other businesses by using the new technique
of ``bundling'' his assets to maximize the revenue he can get. For
example, bundling the Suns and the Diamondbacks in a TV package
might get him more money than selling the TV rights separately.
Colangelo says its all part of getting his house in order, because
at almost 60 years old he's beginning to think of succession
issues. By NENA BAKER. Story will move in the ``S'' category. &QL; 
