Jacobson's disappearance comes and goes and ... what? Cookie's two
teenagers, who admit stuffing their mother's body in a trash bin,
go merrily on with high school? And Cookie's husband, who supports
the kids, remains in the neighborhood of make-believe? While poor
Cookie _ hauled off to a compacting plant, shredded, squeezed into
a dump truck and deposited in a landfill _ crumbles? Yes. By EJ
