<HEADLINE>
BASIC INSTINCTS AND BARE NECESSITIES
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Claiming that it has ``been inundated with requests from
consumers to create something for the millennium'' (Dear Diary:
Today I wrote to General Mills to tell them about my fervent hopes
that they will design a cereal for the millennium), General Mills
has announced Millenios, a Cheerios-like cereal that's added sugar
and the number ``2,'' and taken away one millennium ``n.'' The
company is calling this the ``official cereal of the millennium.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Bruce Feirstein &LR;  writes in Yahoo magazine that a pair of
socks worn by  &UR; Matt Damon &LR;  on the set of ``All the Pretty Horses''
went for $80 at eBay. The seller admitted in his description of the
item that he took the socks while he was on the set.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was walking past the chairs where the stars sit, and on
Matt's chair a pair of sneakers and socks were there. I thought
taking the shoes would be too obvious, so I just took the socks.
This is a piece of good memorabilia by an Oscar-winning actor!''
</P>
<P>
   Shoppers wistful that the socks are gone should take comfort
from the fact that there are currently 106 Damon items for sale
(mostly pictures) at eBay.
</P>
<P>
   _ Designer  &UR; Naomi Leff &LR; , who specializes in ``wildly
influential, incredibly demanding'' clients, told Town &AMP; Country
that the latest in rich person's chic is the two-kitchen home.
</P>
<P>
   ``The kitchen has two functions,'' she said, ``and one of them
is to be a gathering place at the end of the day where the family
can come together. When a family wants to further that idea, and
also the tradition of eating in the kitchen, to capture that old
happy-family feeling, they don't necessarily want the private chef
in there with them.
</P>
<P>
   ``So they have a second kitchen where the real work happens. The
chef is making dinner in one kitchen, and they're eating it in
another.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Kursty Groves &LR; , a graduate of the Royal College of Art in
London, has invented a Techno-Bra, and Discover magazine reports
that it will be on the market by Christmas 2000. The garment will
be made of fabric and electronics that monitor heart rate. If the
wearer is panicked, it sends a radio signal to the police that
identifies its location.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MORE NEIGHBORLY NEWS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Welcome to the neighborhood!'' writes one San Franciscan
after reading architect  &UR; Daniel Solomon &LR; 's description, in
Architectural Digest, of buying a site and building a house in San
Francisco. ``The Marina?'' Solomon says he asked the real estate
agent who sold him the site. ``The Marina is yuppies and
blue-haired ladies, the squarest neighborhood in San Francisco. We
wanted North Beach.''
</P>
<P>
   The architect prides himself on the modesty of his design.
``There was something wonderful about designing a house that merely
tried to manipulate a type and not be a major statement. It's
nonpolemical and deferential to the type of house that makes the
Marina what it is.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Doug Webster &LR;  says the area between the Inner Mission and the
Castro (think Dolores Park) should be called Inny-Outy;
 &UR; Ericka Lutz &LR;  used to live in NoHa, the north side of the Panhandle
from the Haight; and  &UR; Steve Koval &LR; , who lived on Nob Hill bordering
the Tenderloin, called it Sirloin.
</P>
<P>
   _ In Santa Clara, 3Com is growing so rapidly that the company is
planning to offer valet parking for employees, enabling more cars
to be crammed in, reports the Wall Street Journal.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LOVE NOTES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Michael Douglas &LR;  and  &UR; Catherine Zeta-Jones &LR;  are so hot and
heavy that the rumor is they'll announce their engagement Saturday,
his 55th birthday and her 30th. Also going strong:
 &UR; Puffy Combs &LR;  and  &UR; Jennifer Lopez &LR; , who have told friends to save
New Year's Eve for a party in Las Vegas. And  &UR; Jack Nicholson &LR;  and
 &UR; Lara Flynn Boyle &LR; , who the New York Post says met on the set of
``Cannes Man,'' a movie that starred  &UR; Rebecca Broussard &LR; , with whom
Nicholson has had a few kids.
</P>
<P>
   _ Special preferences in the bedroom: At the wedding of Berkeley
Rep's  &UR; Susie Falk &LR;  and lighting designer  &UR; York Kennedy &LR; , the
minister said that in painting the couple's bedroom, Kennedy had
``infused the paint with many cups of Peet's espresso coffee
because Susie is such a fan of Peet's.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm absolutely furious. Do you know when they search you, they
actually touch your breast? ... Why don't they use a hand-held
detector like they do at all the other airports in the world? They
wouldn't touch a man's penis, would they?''
</P>
<P>
   _ Diana Ross, to the London Evening Standard, after being
detained on charges of assault by police at Heathrow Airport. The
singer was searched after she allegedly set off the metal detector.
The security officer told police Ross was so irate that she
assaulted her. Police gave Ross ``a caution,'' said the BBC.
</P>
