<P>
   (NYT32) UNDATED -- Sept. 22, 1999 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT-B&AMP;W, 09-22
-- Wood in contact with the soil will eventually rot. Builders try
to prevent this by supporting framing members of a house, porch or
deck on masonry footings or a concrete foundation. Even with these
precautions it is possible for wood to rot if it gets wet enough
and if the temperature rises above the freezing mark. (Edward R.
Lipinski/New York Times Illustration) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) NEW YORK -- Sept. 22, 1999 -- RADIO-GIANT, 09-22 --
Listening to ``The Jewish Giant'' are Jenny Carchman, far left,
with her grandmother and father, Dorothy and Philip Carchman. The
powerful 25-minute audio documentary on the life of Eddie Carmel,
whose swollen dimensions were the result of acromegaly and were
caused by a tumor on the pituitary gland, will air on National
Public Radio on Oct. 6. (Frances Roberts/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
