Avenue's flagship Manhattan store. Last week Saks, the venerable
clothier to the ladies who lunch, turned 75, but a placid old age
is not in the cards. (Rebecca Cooney/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) UNDATED -- Sept. 22, 1999 -
SUB-MUSEUM-FUNDING-GIULIANI-2, 09-22 -- A portrait of the Virgin
Mary flecked with elephant dung titled ``The Holy Virgin Mary'', by
Chris Ofili. If the directors of the Brooklyn Museum of Art hoped
to provoke the public with such offerings in an exhibition of
cutting-edge British art that opens next week, they may have scored
a publicity coup at the expense of the museum's budget. A catalog
description of this and other pieces so provoked Mayor Rudolph
Giuliani of New York on Wednesday that he vowed to cut funding to
the private but city-subsidized museum until its director ``comes
to his senses.'' (From exhibit catalog ``Sensation'', Thames and
Hudson, 1997/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) TAIPEI, Taiwan -- Sept. 22, 1999 - TAIWAN-QUAKE-2, 09-22
-- Rescue workers use heavy equipment in their search for survivors
early Thursday in a building damaged in Tuesday's earthquake. The
death toll from the powerful quake climbed to over 2,000 people,
with more then 4,000 injured, officials said. Some 2,600 people
were believed to be trapped in rubble, but rescuers were finding
more bodies than survivors as they bored into collapsed houses and
high-rise apartment complexes across central Taiwan. (David L.
Ryan/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) SANTA ROSA, Calif. -- Sept. 22, 1999 -
LIGHTING-STRIKES-FLOATER, 09-22 - Lighting erupts over Santa Rosa
early Wednesday as leftover moisture from Hurricane Hillary was
funneled north bringing simultaneous lightning strikes and heavy
downpours. The photo was taken on the North End of Fountain Grove
on Skyfarm Drive viewing the Santa Rosa Plain to the west. (Kent
Porter/Santa Rosa Press-Democrat) LITE
</P>
<P>
